"Dirty Laundry" is a hit song written by Don Henley and Danny Kortchmar, from Henley's Gold album I Can't Stand Still, released in 1982. The song hit #1 on the Billboard chart in October 1982, as a 45. Lyrically, the song describes mass media sensationalism and yellow journalism.

Released as the second single from I Can't Stand Still, it spent four weeks at #3 on the Billboard Hot 100 in early 1983. The single was certified Gold by the Recording Industry Association of America, representing sales of over one million records in the US.
